{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm from Detroit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6920,"text":"A city that in the 1950s\nwas the world's industrial giant,"},{"time":12760,"text":"with a population of 1.8 million people"},{"time":15520,"text":"and 140 square miles\nof land and infrastructure,"},{"time":20120,"text":"used to support this booming,\nMidwestern urban center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25040,"text":"And now today,"},{"time":27160,"text":"just a half a century later,"},{"time":29920,"text":"Detroit is the poster child\nfor urban decay."},{"time":34200,"text":"Currently in Detroit,\nour population is under 700,000,"},{"time":38360,"text":"of which 84 percent are African American,"},{"time":41840,"text":"and due to decades of disinvestment"},{"time":45920,"text":"and capital flight"},{"time":48080,"text":"from the city into the suburbs,"},{"time":52000,"text":"there is a scarcity in Detroit."},{"time":55120,"text":"There is a scarcity of retail,"},{"time":57640,"text":"more specifically, fresh food retail,"},{"time":62960,"text":"resulting in a city\nwhere 70 percent of Detroiters"},{"time":66600,"text":"are obese and overweight,"},{"time":69240,"text":"and they struggle."},{"time":71160,"text":"They struggle to access\nnutritious food that they need,"},{"time":75600,"text":"that they need to stay healthy,"},{"time":78880,"text":"that they need to prevent premature\nillness and diet-related diseases."},{"time":83800,"text":"Far too many Detroiters\nlive closer to a fast food restaurant"},{"time":89520,"text":"or to a convenience store,\nor to a gas station"},{"time":92840,"text":"where they have to shop for food"},{"time":94920,"text":"than they do a full-service supermarket."},{"time":99680,"text":"And this is not good news\nabout the city of Detroit,"},{"time":104960,"text":"but this is the news"},{"time":108200,"text":"and the story"},{"time":109600,"text":"that Detroiters intend to change."},{"time":112600,"text":"No, I'm going to take that back."},{"time":115000,"text":"This is the story\nthat Detroiters are changing,"},{"time":119360,"text":"through urban agriculture\nand food entrepreneurship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124080,"text":"Here's the thing:"},{"time":125520,"text":"because of Detroit's recent history,"},{"time":127920,"text":"it now finds itself"},{"time":130000,"text":"with some very unique assets,"},{"time":133600,"text":"open land being one of them."},{"time":136600,"text":"Experts say that the entire cities\nof Boston, San Francisco,"},{"time":141680,"text":"and the borough of Manhattan"},{"time":143240,"text":"will fit in the land area\nof the city of Detroit."},{"time":147040,"text":"They further go on to say"},{"time":148600,"text":"that 40 square miles\nof the city is vacant."},{"time":153040,"text":"That's a quarter to a third of the city,"},{"time":155920,"text":"and with that level of emptiness,"},{"time":157720,"text":"it creates a landscape\nunlike any other big city."},{"time":162840,"text":"So Detroit has this --\nopen land, fertile soil,"},{"time":168040,"text":"proximity to water,"},{"time":170080,"text":"willing labor"},{"time":171880,"text":"and a desperate demand\nfor healthy, fresh food."},{"time":175480,"text":"All of this has created\na people-powered grassroots movement"},{"time":180040,"text":"of people in Detroit"},{"time":181600,"text":"who are transforming this city"},{"time":183760,"text":"from what was the capital\nof American industry"},{"time":187760,"text":"into an agrarian paradise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190306,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191480,"text":"You know, I think,\nout of all the cities in the world,"},{"time":195560,"text":"Detroit, Michigan, is best positioned\nto serve as the world's urban exemplar"},{"time":201360,"text":"of food security\nand sustainable development."},{"time":204920,"text":"In Detroit, we have over 1,500, yes, 1,500"},{"time":209960,"text":"gardens and farms\nlocated all across the city today."},{"time":214640,"text":"And these aren't plots of land"},{"time":216200,"text":"where we're just growing\ntomatoes and carrots either."},{"time":219640,"text":"You understand, urban agriculture\nin Detroit is all about community,"},{"time":224160,"text":"because we grow together."},{"time":226040,"text":"So these spaces\nare spaces of conviviality."},{"time":229440,"text":"These spaces are places\nwhere we're building social cohesion"},{"time":233440,"text":"as well as providing healthy, fresh food"},{"time":237840,"text":"to our friends, our families\nand our neighbors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241200,"text":"Come walk with me."},{"time":242760,"text":"I want to take you\nthrough a few Detroit neighborhoods,"},{"time":245400,"text":"and I want you to see what it looks like\nwhen you empower local leadership,"},{"time":249800,"text":"and when you support grassroots movements"},{"time":252760,"text":"of folks who are moving the needle\nin low-income communities"},{"time":256600,"text":"and people of color."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258160,"text":"Our first stop, Oakland Avenue Farms."},{"time":261240,"text":"Oakland Avenue Farms is located\nin Detroit's North End neighborhood."},{"time":266440,"text":"Oakland Avenue Farms is transforming\ninto a five-acre landscape"},{"time":271160,"text":"combining art, architecture,\nsustainable ecologies"},{"time":275280,"text":"and new market practices."},{"time":277360,"text":"In the truest sense of the word,"},{"time":279120,"text":"this is what agriculture\nlooks like in the city of Detroit."},{"time":284800,"text":"I've had the opportunity\nto work with Oakland Avenue Farms"},{"time":288680,"text":"in hosting Detroit-grown and made\nfarm-to-table dinners."},{"time":293440,"text":"These are dinners\nwhere we bring folks onto the farm,"},{"time":296520,"text":"we give them plenty\nof time and opportunity"},{"time":299000,"text":"to meet and greet and talk to the grower,"},{"time":302120,"text":"and then they're taken on a farm tour."},{"time":304320,"text":"And then afterwards,\nthey're treated to a farm-to-table meal"},{"time":310120,"text":"prepared by a chef"},{"time":312080,"text":"who showcases all the produce on the farm\nright at the peak of its freshness."},{"time":318320,"text":"We do that."},{"time":319560,"text":"We bring people onto the farm,"},{"time":321480,"text":"we have folks sitting around a table,"},{"time":323720,"text":"because we want to change\npeople's relationship to food."},{"time":327080,"text":"We want them to know\nexactly where their food comes from"},{"time":331360,"text":"that is grown on that farm\nthat's on the plate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335200,"text":"My second stop,"},{"time":336800,"text":"I'm going to take you\non the west side of Detroit,"},{"time":339480,"text":"to the Brightmoor neighborhood."},{"time":341280,"text":"Now, Brightmoor is\na lower-income community in Detroit."},{"time":344720,"text":"There's about 13,000\nresidents in Brightmoor."},{"time":348240,"text":"They decided to take\na block-by-block-by-block strategy."},{"time":353280,"text":"So within the neighborhood of Brightmoor,"},{"time":355800,"text":"you'll find a 21-block microneighborhood\ncalled Brightmoor Farmway."},{"time":361160,"text":"Now, what was a notorious,\nunsafe, underserved community"},{"time":366440,"text":"has transformed into a welcoming,\nbeautiful, safe farmway,"},{"time":371200,"text":"lush with parks and gardens\nand farms and greenhouses."},{"time":375720,"text":"This tight-knit community\nalso came together recently,"},{"time":378960,"text":"and they purchased an abandoned building,"},{"time":381360,"text":"an abandoned building\nthat was in disrepair and in foreclosure."},{"time":385840,"text":"And with the help of friends\nand families and volunteers,"},{"time":389040,"text":"they were able to take down\nthe bulletproof glass,"},{"time":391800,"text":"they were able to clean up the grounds"},{"time":393680,"text":"and they transformed that building\ninto a community kitchen,"},{"time":397520,"text":"into a cafe, into a storefront."},{"time":400320,"text":"Now the farmers and the food artisans\nwho live in Brightmoor,"},{"time":404120,"text":"they have a place where they\ncan make and sell their product."},{"time":407240,"text":"And the people in the community"},{"time":408800,"text":"have some place where they can buy\nhealthy, fresh food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412720,"text":"Urban agriculture --\nand this is my third example --"},{"time":415360,"text":"can be used as a way to lift up\nthe business cooperative model."},{"time":420960,"text":"The 1,500 farms and gardens\nI told you about earlier?"},{"time":425000,"text":"Keep Growing Detroit\nis a nonprofit organization"},{"time":427280,"text":"that had a lot to do with those farms."},{"time":430800,"text":"They distributed last year\n70,000 packets of seeds"},{"time":435800,"text":"and a quarter of a million transplants,"},{"time":439360,"text":"and as a result of that last year,"},{"time":441440,"text":"550,000 pounds of produce"},{"time":445360,"text":"was grown in the city of Detroit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454880,"text":"But aside from all of that,"},{"time":456920,"text":"they also manage\nand operate a cooperative."},{"time":460520,"text":"It's called Grown in Detroit."},{"time":462440,"text":"It consists of about 70 farmers,"},{"time":465720,"text":"small farmers."},{"time":467240,"text":"They all grow, and they sell together."},{"time":471160,"text":"They grow fruits,"},{"time":473600,"text":"they grow vegetables,"},{"time":475520,"text":"they grow flowers,"},{"time":477320,"text":"they grow herbs in healthy soil,"},{"time":480280,"text":"free of chemicals,\npesticides, fertilizers,"},{"time":483240,"text":"genetically modified products --"},{"time":485600,"text":"healthy food."},{"time":487520,"text":"And when their product is sold"},{"time":489560,"text":"all over the city of Detroit\nin local markets,"},{"time":492440,"text":"they get a hundred percent\nof the proceeds from the sale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496920,"text":"In a city like Detroit,"},{"time":499320,"text":"where far too many, far too many\nAfrican Americans are dying"},{"time":504800,"text":"as a result of diet-related diseases,"},{"time":508400,"text":"restaurants, they have a huge role to play"},{"time":511440,"text":"in increasing healthy food access\nin the city of Detroit,"},{"time":514880,"text":"culturally appropriate restaurants."},{"time":517320,"text":"Enter Detroit Vegan Soul."},{"time":519080,"text":"Yes, we have a vegan soul food restaurant\nin the city of Detroit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525800,"text":"Yes, yes."},{"time":528200,"text":"Detroit Vegan Soul\nis providing Detroiters the opportunity"},{"time":532280,"text":"to eat more plant-based meals"},{"time":535720,"text":"and they've received an overwhelming\nresponse from Detroiters."},{"time":539520,"text":"Detroiters are hungry\nfor culturally appropriate,"},{"time":542080,"text":"fresh, delicious food."},{"time":544720,"text":"That's why we built a nonprofit\norganization called FoodLab Detroit,"},{"time":548480,"text":"to help small neighborhood\nburgeoning food entrepreneurs"},{"time":551600,"text":"start and scale healthy food businesses."},{"time":554840,"text":"FoodLab provides\nthese entrepreneurs incubation,"},{"time":558320,"text":"hands-on education, workshops,"},{"time":560760,"text":"technical assistance,\naccess to industry experts"},{"time":564160,"text":"so that they can grow and scale."},{"time":566600,"text":"They're very small businesses,"},{"time":568080,"text":"but last year, they had a combined revenue"},{"time":571360,"text":"of over 7.5 million dollars,"},{"time":573920,"text":"and they provided 252 jobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577240,"text":"Listen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578480,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581280,"text":"These are just a few examples"},{"time":585240,"text":"on how you expand opportunities"},{"time":589240,"text":"so that everybody can participate"},{"time":592720,"text":"and prosper,"},{"time":594120,"text":"particularly those\nwho come from neighborhoods"},{"time":598120,"text":"that have been historically excluded\nfrom these types of opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602880,"text":"I know, I know."},{"time":605880,"text":"My city is a long way from succeeding."},{"time":610040,"text":"We're still struggling,"},{"time":611480,"text":"and I'm not going to stand here\non this stage and tell you"},{"time":614320,"text":"that all of Detroit's problems\nand all of Detroit's challenges"},{"time":617760,"text":"are going to be solved\nthrough urban agriculture."},{"time":620720,"text":"I'm not going to do that,"},{"time":622400,"text":"but I will tell you this:"},{"time":624520,"text":"urban agriculture\nhas Detroit thinking about its city"},{"time":627920,"text":"now in a different way,"},{"time":629520,"text":"a city that can be both urban and rural."},{"time":634000,"text":"And yes, I know, these stories are small,"},{"time":636680,"text":"these stories are\nneighborhood-based stories,"},{"time":639560,"text":"but these stories are powerful."},{"time":641640,"text":"They're powerful because I'm showing you\nhow we're creating a new society"},{"time":645480,"text":"left vacant in the places and the spaces\nthat was disintegration from the old."},{"time":651280,"text":"They're powerful stories\nbecause they're stories about love,"},{"time":654640,"text":"the love that Detroiters have\nfor one another,"},{"time":656840,"text":"the love that we have for our community,\nthe love that we have for Mother Earth,"},{"time":660680,"text":"but more importantly,\nthese stories are stories"},{"time":663200,"text":"on how devastation, despair, decay"},{"time":668240,"text":"never ever get the last word\nin the city of Detroit."},{"time":673120,"text":"When hundreds of thousands\nof people left Detroit,"},{"time":676160,"text":"and they left us for dead,\nthose who stayed had hope."},{"time":679440,"text":"They held on to hope."},{"time":681240,"text":"They never gave up."},{"time":682560,"text":"They always kept fighting."},{"time":685200,"text":"And listen, I know,"},{"time":686480,"text":"transforming a big city like Detroit\nto one that is prosperous,"},{"time":690480,"text":"one that's functional, one that's healthy,"},{"time":692960,"text":"one that's inclusive,\none that provides opportunities for all,"},{"time":696120,"text":"I know it's tough,"},{"time":697680,"text":"I know it's challenging, I know it's hard."},{"time":700080,"text":"But I just believe"},{"time":702080,"text":"that if we start strengthening\nthe social fabric of our communities,"},{"time":705680,"text":"and if we kickstart economic opportunities\nin our most vulnerable neighborhoods,"},{"time":710760,"text":"it all starts with healthy, accessible,"},{"time":714920,"text":"delicious, culturally appropriate food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719120,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":726800,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}